  <description><![CDATA[<p>Best Western Plus Executive Hotel and Suites is in prime location for exploring <a data-udi="umb://document/65aa4a2626424153a1c1c3685d2607aa" href="/{localLink:umb://document/65aa4a2626424153a1c1c3685d2607aa}" title="Turin">Turin</a>. If you're after somewhere modern and comfortable for your city break, this is a great choice.</p>
<p>The rooms are bright and modern, with fresh white bed linen and comfortable mattresses - they even have tea and coffee making facilities, so you can get your day off to a good start with a fresh brew. When it comes to breakfast, you'll have lots to choose from - we love that it's all fresh from the pastries to the fruit. They make the coffee to order too so grab that Italian espresso before heading into the City.</p>
<p>The location is perfect, you can either hop on a metro or take a leisurely stroll along the River Po into the centre of Turin. Head to Piazza Vittorio Veneto for chilled aperitivo in the early evening - you should be able to spot the snow-capped peaks of the Alps from there. The hotel's in the San Salvario district, where you'll find lots of nice places for dinner. The staff here have some great recommendations, so just ask. It's a short walk to the train station, which means it's easy to take day trips to places like Milan, only an hour or so away.</p>
<p>Back at the hotel there's ample opportunity to relax. If you're here in the summer head to the solarium on the panoramic roof terrace. You can cool off in the hydro-massage pool or just enjoy the views. There's also a wellness centre (open Sep - Jun) with a whirlpool and sauna, so you can relax after a busy day in the city.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 35 mins by private car.</p>]]></description>
